 The University of Mpumalanga has suspended members of the SRC following a class boycott that started last week Tuesday. The president of SRC Mcolisi Ngcamphalala and Wandile Shabangu, the Treasurer of the SRC and Mbombela CRC chairperson, have been suspended. The student representatives say the University has sent Fidelity security to remove the two from campus. ‪The students have been protesting accusing management of corruption and nepotism. ALSO READ: Students boycott classes at university On Tuesday they blocked the road to the university demanding that management address their concerns. Watch video supplied by a security guard on the campus.  ALSO READ:Student protesters close gates at University of Mpumalanga